<div id="node-3286" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3286" title="Spring Data JDBC Extensions with Oracle Database Support 1.0.0.RC1 Released">Spring Data JDBC Extensions with Oracle Database Support 1.0.0.RC1 Released</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Thomas Risberg on Tue, 2011-10-18 08:27        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>Dear Spring Community,  We are pleased to announce that the release candidate (1.0.0.RC1) of the Spring Data JDBC Extensions 1.0 project with Oracle Database support is now available!</p>
<p>The new Spring Data JDBC Extensions project was created to provide additional support for vendor specific JDBC extensions as well as new approaches to working with JDBC like QueryDSL. The bulk of the support is made up of code ported from the SpringSource project &quot;Advanced Pack for Oracle Database&quot; that was available for support subscription customers. We are now making this code available to all Spring users and any new developments will be made in the Spring Data JDBC Extensions project.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.springsource.com/download/community?project=Spring%20Data%20JDBC">Downloads</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-data/data-jdbc/docs/1.0.0.RC1/api/">JavaDocs</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-data/data-jdbc/docs/1.0.0.RC1/reference/html/">Reference Documentation</a> | <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-data/data-jdbc/docs/1.0.0.RC1/changelog.txt">Changelog</a></p>
<p>To learn more about the project, visit the Spring Data JDBC Extensions <a href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-data/jdbc-extensions">Homepage</a>.</p>
<p>The improvements in Spring Data JDBC Extensions 1.0.0.RC1 include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Added documentation chapter for QueryDSL SQL module</li>
<li>Added OSGi manifests</li>
<li>Fixed slf4j/log4j and other dependencies</li>
</ul>
<p>I'd like to thank Andrei Stefan for the JPetStore re-write using the QueryDSL support and SQLFire. It provides a good example for using the QueryDslJdbcTemplate in a project - see <a href="https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-sqlfire-samples">https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-sqlfire-samples</a>.</p>
<p>Looking forward to your feedback on the <a href="http://forum.springsource.org/forumdisplay.php?f=27">forum</a> or in the <a href="https://jira.springsource.org/browse/DATAJDBC">issue tracker</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
<div id="node-3285" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3285" title="Paris &quot;What&#039;s Next&quot; Talks on SQLFire and RabbitMQ ">Paris &quot;What&#039;s Next&quot; Talks on SQLFire and RabbitMQ </a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Josh Long on Mon, 2011-10-17 14:08        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
     
<div style="float: right; width:200px; padding: 10px"><a href="http://www.infoq.com/presentations/Multi-Platform-Messaging-with-RabbitMQ"><img width="200" border="0" alt="Rob Harrop introducing RabbitMQ and multi-platform messaging" src="/files/u41069/pwn_rabbitmq_robharrop_min.jpg" /></a></div>
<p><a href="http://www.infoq.com/">InfoQ</a> has published two more great talks from  the <a href="http://www.whatsnextparis.com/">What's Next&quot;</a>  conference in Paris.      These talks dovetail nicely with the keynote that <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3200">Adrian Colyer gave discussing enterprise applications and beyond.</a></p>
 
<p>Both of these talks highlight technologies that can help you scale your Spring applications.   The <a href="http://www.infoq.com/presentations/Multi-Platform-Messaging-with-RabbitMQ">first talk, by Rob Harrop</a> - now a RabbitMQ engineer and formerly a  contributor to both the Spring framework  and the SpringSource dmServer project -  introduces multi-platform messaging using <a href="http://www.rabbitmq.com">RabbitMQ</a>.  The talk includes demonstrations in many languages  including Java, Python, Ruby and Erlang  - and      highlights the power of RabbitMQ as a communications bus between components in an architecture.</p>
 
<div style="float: left; width:200px; padding: 10px"><a href="http://www.infoq.com/presentations/SQLFire-Scalable-SQL-instead-of-NoSQL"><img width="200" border="0" alt="Jags Ramnarayan, chief architect for GemFire at VMWare, introduces SQLFire" src="/files/u41069/pwn_sqlfire_jags2_min.jpg" /></a></div>
<p>The <a href="http://www.infoq.com/presentations/SQLFire-Scalable-SQL-instead-of-NoSQL">second talk, by Jags Ramnarayan</a>, chief architect for GemFire at VMWare, introduces    <a href="http://www.vmware.com/products/datacenter-virtualization/vfabric-sqlfire/overview.html">SQLFire</a> a scalable SQL database that offers a compelling alternative to NOSQL. Jags  explains  how SQL can be used for modern data stores backing online highly scalable applications by using a different consistency model and shared-nothing persistence.</p>
 
<p>Many thanks to <a href="http://www.infoq.com">InfoQ</a> for  covering these great  What's Next talks and providing these outstanding presentations to the community.</p>  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
<div id="node-3253" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3280" title="Spring Integration 2.1 M2 Released">Spring Integration 2.1 M2 Released</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Josh Long on Thu, 2011-10-13 18:53        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>We are pleased to announce that <a href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-integration">Spring Integration</a> 2.1 Milestone 2 is now available. 74 issues were addressed  <a href="https://jira.springsource.org/secure/ReleaseNote.jspa?projectId=10121&amp;version=12200">as listed in the release notes</a>.   The JARs are available in the SpringSource Milestone Maven Repository, and the distribution download is available from the <a href="http://www.springsource.com/download/community">SpringSource Community Download</a> page. All docs (reference manual and JavaDoc) are <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-integration/docs/2.1.x/">here</a>.</p>
<p>Chief among the many new improvements are:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Refactored (simpler and more flexible) Aggregator/Resequencer</li>
    <li>An XPath filter</li>
    <li>Stored Procedure adapters</li>
    <li>AMQP-backed Message Channels</li>
</ul>  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
